bug.short_desc: PHP Debug option "Break at First Line" broken (can't be unchecked)

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86768 Screenshot of the About Eclipse Platform Plug-ins window for you to see the PDT plug-in versions
Build ID: M20071023-1652
Steps To Reproduce: 1. Open Eclipse. 2. Go to the Window menu and then Preferences. 3. Go to the Debug submenu under PHP. 4. Uncheck the "Break at First Line" option. 5. Try to debug or open Preferences again and it will be checked.
More information: It seems that the preferences can't be saved, because if I switch the debugger from Zend to XDebug and the OK to the dialog, when I open it again, it keeps using Zend. This doesn't happens with other options such as the PHP Editor options, for example, and makes me think that it is a problem with the Debug module options only. My version of PDT is 1.0.1.
This has been fixed since the M1 release, so should be in the next release of PDT.
